   "source": [
    "# Chapter 8: The De-Industrialization Pulse - Step-by-Step Proofs\n",
    "\n",
    "This Jupyter notebook provides a step-by-step verification of the claims, equations, and figures from Chapter 8 of *The Renewables Migration* by Vincenzo Grimaldi. We will explore the **Survival Bridge**, **Carbon Recovery**, and the **Relocation Math** concepts.\n",
    "\n",
    "## Setup"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import seaborn as sns\n",
    "from chapter8_core import Chapter8Engine\n",
    "\n",
    "# Initialize the engine\n",
    "engine = Chapter8Engine()\n",
    "metrics = engine.metrics\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"Chapter 8 Engine Initialized\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 8.1 The Survival Bridge: Legacy Costs vs. MCP-Optimized Reality (Figure 8.1)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "intensities, legacy_costs, mcp_costs = engine.get_survival_bridge_data()\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))\n",
    "plt.plot(intensities, legacy_costs, \'r--\', label=\'Legacy Market Rate (0.20 €/kWh)\')\n",
    "plt.plot(intensities, mcp_costs, \'b-\', label=\'MCP-Optimized Rate (2030 Roadmap)\')\n",
    "plt.axhline(y=metrics[\'Mittelstand_Death_Zone\'], color=\'orange\', linestyle=\':\', label=\'Mittelstand Death Zone (0.15 €/kWh)\')\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.xlabel(\'Energy Intensity (kWh/€ GVA)\')\n",
    "plt.ylabel(\'Net Energy Cost (€/kWh)\')\n",
    "plt.title(\'Figure 8.1: The Survival Bridge\')\n",
    "plt.legend()\n",
    "plt.grid(True, linestyle=\'--\', alpha=0.7)\n",
    "plt.show()\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"Book Claim: Legacy Market Rate: €{metrics[\\\'Legacy_Market_Rate\\\']:.2f}/kWh.\")\n",
    "print(f\"Book Claim: Mittelstand Death Zone: €{metrics[\\\'Mittelstand_Death_Zone\\\']:.2f}/kWh.\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 8.5.1 The Protocol-Enabled Carbon Recovery Equation\n",
    "\n",
    "$C_{MCP} = \sum C_{api} \cdot (CO_{2,global} - CO_{2,DE}) \cdot \Phi_{MCP}$\n",
    "\n",
    "This equation quantifies the emissions avoided by retaining industry through MCP-enabled cost optimization."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from ipywidgets import interact, FloatSlider\n",
    "\n",
    "def carbon_recovery_simulator(capacity_retained, co2_global, co2_de, phi_mcp):\n",
    "    c_mcp = engine.calculate_carbon_recovery(capacity_retained, co2_global, co2_de, phi_mcp)\n",
    "    print(f\"Sovereign Carbon Recovery (C_MCP): {c_mcp:.1f} Mt CO2\")\n",
    "\n",
    "interact(carbon_recovery_simulator,\n",
    "         capacity_retained=FloatSlider(min=1, max=100, step=1, value=35, description=\'Capacity (Mt)\'),\n",
    "         co2_global=FloatSlider(min=1.0, max=2.5, step=0.1, value=1.8, description=\'Global CO2\'),\n",
    "         co2_de=FloatSlider(min=0.1, max=1.0, step=0.1, value=0.6, description=\'German CO2\'),\n",
    "         phi_mcp=FloatSlider(min=0.1, max=1.0, step=0.05, value=0.8, description=\'Retention Factor\'))\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"Book Claim: Prevents {metrics[\\\'Annual_Prevented_Leakage\\\']:.0f} Mt of annual global leakage.\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 8.6 The Polynomial of Relocation: The 2030 Strategic Pivot\n",
    "\n",
    "$R = 250E + 80R + 50I + 30D - \\Psi_{MCP}$\n",
    "\n",
    "This equation models the relocation pressure (R) and how the Protocol Offset (Psi_MCP) neutralizes the primary driver of factory flight."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def relocation_simulator(e, r, i, d, psi_mcp_ratio):\n",
    "    relocation_pressure = engine.calculate_relocation_polynomial(e, r, i, d, psi_mcp_ratio)\n",
    "    print(f\"Relocation Pressure (R): {relocation_pressure:.1f}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "interact(relocation_simulator,\n",
    "         e=FloatSlider(min=0.0, max=1.0, step=0.1, value=0.5, description=\'Energy Gap (E)\'),\n",
    "         r=FloatSlider(min=0.0, max=1.0, step=0.1, value=0.3, description=\'Resilience (R)\'),\n",
    "         i=FloatSlider(min=0.0, max=1.0, step=0.1, value=0.2, description=\'Inertia Gap (I)\'),\n",
    "         d=FloatSlider(min=0.0, max=1.0, step=0.1, value=0.4, description=\'Dependency (D)\'),\n",
    "         psi_mcp_ratio=FloatSlider(min=0.0, max=1.0, step=0.05, value=0.6, description=\'Protocol Offset\'))\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"Book Claim: Protocol Offset (Psi_MCP) offsets {metrics[\\\'Protocol_Offset_Target\\\']:.0%} of the energy gap (E).\")"
   ]
  }
